Former Governor of Imo State, Emeka Ihedioha has on Wednesday officially approached the Supreme court of Nigeria, led my by Justice Tanko Muhammed to review a Judgement delivered against him and his party the People’s Democratic Party, PDP. Ihedioha heads for S’Court to seek judgment review Reall that  Hon. Emeka Ihedioha, of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), was to meet with the Supreme Court for a review of its judgment of January 14, 2020 in which it declared Senator Hope Uzodinma of the All Progressives Congress (APC) as governor of the state. Details shortly…